    "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI've had a regression in one of my app by migrating from React 17 to React 18, and more specifically, by switching from `ReactDOM.render` to `ReactDOM.createRoot`.\r\n\r\nNow, I know that this switch has some breaking changes. So I'm not sure if this is a real bug (meaning maybe it's an acceptable bug due to an accepted breaking change). But in that case, maybe the documentation could be enhance with that example.\r\n\r\nBasically, I have a Popup component that is using some event listenenr on window in order to react to global clicks (and close). By switching from `render` to `createRoot`, it looks like the rendering of the popup is done before the end of the processing of the event opening that same popup (hence, creating an issue of not showing the popup because it closes right after opening).\r\n\r\nReact version: 18.2.0\r\n\r\n## Steps To Reproduce\r\n\r\nReproduce repository link (with explaination in README): https://github.com/Vinorcola/React-18-event-issue\r\n\r\n## The current behavior\r\n\r\nThe popup does not shows because it closes right after opening.\r\n\r\n## The expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe popup opens on the button click.",
