    "active_lock_reason": null,
    "body": "When using `window.onerror` in the bootstrap script that is hosted in a CDN the error message will show `\"Script error.\"` instead of a proper error message. This is because of the [cross-origin](https://blog.sentry.io/2016/05/17/what-is-script-error/) script. To fix this issue a `crossorigin=\"anonymous\"` attribute needs to be added in the script tag.\r\n\r\nCurrently, `bootstrapScripts` supports [`src` and `integrity`](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/0fce6bb498357feb4465859912004b2e20fe7084/packages/react-dom-bindings/src/server/ReactDOMServerFormatConfig.js#L226) as configurations, should it also supports a `crossorigin` property?\r\n\r\n",
